{
  "texts": [
    "The p-value is estimated via permutation testing.",
    "It is then adjusted to control the false discovery rate (Benjamini and Hochberg, 1995).",
    "Figure 3 demonstrates that the average pretraining boost is significant in every configuration of the experiment.",
    "This finding replicates that from Gururangan et al. (2020).",
    "After averaging across settings for m, n, and the 2 LM types, only two of the 25 classification tasks had a pretraining boost less than 0, and both were greater than -1%."
  ]
}